OL,3,COne punch killer's mum jailed after
OL,4,Ctrying to stop police getting his phone
OL,6,F"The police, of course, retrieved that
OL,7,Finformation. It was capable of being
OL,8,Fused and was used at the trial. It did
OL,9,Fnot have any detrimental effect on the
OL,10,FCrown's ability to prosecute the trial.
OL,12,F"She made a very serious error of
OL,13,Fjudgement out of misguided loyalty.
OL,14,FShe, deep down, did not want the
OL,15,Fpolice to have the phone and
OL,16,Frecognises the extreme error of her
OL,17,Fconduct in that respect.
OL,19,F"It was wholly and utterly out of her
OL,20,Fcharacter."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G11/18
